<span id="viii.v.iv.vii"></span>

<span id="viii.v.iv.vii-p1"></span> <span id="page_95">p. 95</span>
<span id="viii.v.iv.vii-Page_95"></span><span class="c4"><span
id="viii.v.iv.vii-p1.1"></span>Canon VII.</span>

<span id="viii.v.iv.vii-p2"></span><span class="sc"><span
id="viii.v.iv.vii-p2.1"></span>If</span> any one shall presume to take
the fruits offered to the Church, or to give them out of the Church,
without the consent of the bishop, or of the person charged with such
things, and shall refuse to act according to his judgment, let him be
anathema.

<span id="viii.v.iv.vii-p3"></span><span class="sc"><span
id="viii.v.iv.vii-p3.1"></span>Ancient Epitome of Canon VII.</span>

<span id="viii.v.iv.vii-p4"></span>*Whoso performs church acts contrary
to the will of a bishop or of a presbyter, let him be anathema.*

